COLL_OBJECT_REMARKS: INTERNAL NOTES: Preparator notes: completed and set for drying Jan 30, 2018. Several days later, a rotten smell was noticed. Head and especially feet smelled of rot. Feb 6 I cut the feet off at the ankles and placed in a ziploc full of salt. I packed borax into leg stubs on the torso and sewed them shut lightly. Feb 13 I put legs into a fresh ziploc of salt. Legs still had a strong rotten smell but were dry and hard. Head still has a noticeable, but much lighter odor. I dropped iso alcohol into cotton in hawk's eyes; Right hind claw seems deformed.
